726206f-b.title: Queens: Braddock Avenue - Gettysburg Street
726206f-b.text:
Braddock Ave., north side (Rocky Hill Road), east of Gettysburg
Street (Hamilton Ave.). This house does not appear in the 1928 Queens
Atlas. Evidently it was demolished to make way for some two story
brick structures. Some of the occupants were Mrs. Kissam, 1873; B.T.
Eissam Estate, 1891; and one Wolfert, 1869. This farm contained 33.1
acres. This is a set of 3 views.
January 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
